text: Pronunciation is a way a word is usually spoken. It can be affected by many different factors: # Geographical location or dialect # Presence of speech defect # Ethnic group # Education level # Social class Mispronunciation is an actual mistake in speaking. It is not used for how a speaker of a dialect pronounces a word. Examples occur in many place names and personal names. For instance, Leicester Square is actually pronounced like "Lester Square". ==Related pages== *Phonetics *Accent * Dialect ** Dialects of English * Register of a language
title: Pronunciation
